<p>Six major carriers paused flights to and from Venezuela after the U.S. Federal Aviation Administration warned pilots of security risks and “heightened military activity” in and around the country’s airspace [france24.com#1][aljazeera.com#1]. The alert, which urged pilots to “exercise caution” and flagged a “potentially hazardous situation” over Venezuela, comes amid increased U.S. military presence in the region as President Trump steps up pressure on President Nicolás Maduro’s government [washingtonpost.com#1][straitstimes.com#1][firstpost.com#1][france24.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/yVyGSAoYEmOu9sMzCJiQDKlzp-wbHMpAcG00R6Ks8tqc-kjI9GwO5yPJ3dwzQ0gtCHsnfA57S3OyFRs6p0xLpCt_qMV3uV4mWjHiLN_oJIZl39VU9o69nCSIvil6OkOyiHVzyoYGZImXC2MNx2NVoyzftd14S7EIi5o' alt='Airlines suspend flights to and from Venezuela after an FAA security warning about the country’s airspace.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Safety alert: The FAA advised pilots to “exercise caution” due to a “potentially hazardous situation” and a security risk in and around Venezuelan airspace [washingtonpost.com#1][straitstimes.com#1][aljazeera.com#1][firstpost.com#1]</li><li>Airlines’ response: Six major carriers suspended services to Venezuela following the FAA warning of “heightened military activity,” with several airlines canceling flights [france24.com#1][straitstimes.com#1][firstpost.com#1]</li><li>Regional tensions: The notice comes amid a growing American military buildup in the region and intensified U.S. pressure on Nicolás Maduro’s government [washingtonpost.com#1][france24.com#1]</li><li>Traveler impact: Flight suspensions are likely to disrupt itineraries to and from Venezuela as carriers adjust routes and schedules [common]</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Federal Aviation Administration (FAA): The regulator warned of a security risk and urged pilots to “exercise caution” in and around Venezuelan airspace [washingtonpost.com#1][straitstimes.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.w